The paper deals with the extension of a language for ontology design patterns, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence and knowledge representation (cs.AI, cs.LO). The paper also presents new language constructs that increase the expressivity and generality of the language, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper demonstrates the use of these constructs in an application domain, which could be related to databases (cs.DB).
